ğŸ’¾ BACKUP INFORMATION
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Each setup script creates timestamped backups:

hypridle.conf backup: ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf.backup.TIMESTAMP
WindowRules backup:   ~/.config/hypr/UserConfigs/WindowRules.conf.backup.TIMESTAMP

To restore:
  cp ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf.backup.* ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf
  cp ~/.config/hypr/UserConfigs/WindowRules.conf.backup.* \
     ~/.config/hypr/UserConfigs/WindowRules.conf
  hyprctl reload


ğŸ”§ CUSTOMIZATION (AFTER SETUP)
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Change timeout:
  Edit: ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf
  Find: "timeout = 150"
  Change to: "timeout = 180" (or whatever you want in seconds)

Change ASCII art:
  For Symphony: ~/.config/hypr/branding/symphony.txt
  For Omarchy: ~/.config/screensaver/art.txt

Change effects:
  Edit screensaver-cmd script
  Find: --random-effect
  Options: matrix, fireworks, rain, decrypt, synthgrid, blackhole, etc.


â“ COMMON QUESTIONS
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Q: Will this break my Hyprland?
A: NO - Zero crash risk, changes are append-only with backups

Q: Can I use both screensavers?
A: YES - Use different timeouts (150s + 180s)

Q: How do I test without waiting?
A: screensaver-launch (manual trigger)

Q: What if something goes wrong?
A: Restore from backup (automated) or manual undo

Q: Is TTE installed?
A: Probably not - use sudo pacman -S python-terminaltexteffects

Q: How do I uninstall?
A: Restore backup OR manually delete the added sections


ğŸš¨ IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

Three levels of undo:

1. Automatic (Recommended):
   cp ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf.backup.* ~/.config/hypr/hypridle.conf
   cp ~/.config/hypr/UserConfigs/WindowRules.conf.backup.* \
      ~/.config/hypr/UserConfigs/WindowRules.conf
   hyprctl reload

2. Manual:
   Remove the listener section from hypridle.conf
   Remove the window rules from WindowRules.conf
   hyprctl reload

3. Nuclear:
   Super+Shift+R (reload Hyprland keyboard shortcut)
   Or: Ctrl+Alt+Backspace (emergency restart)


âœ¨ WHAT'S INCLUDED IN EACH SETUP SCRIPT
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

setup-symphony-screensaver.sh:
  âœ“ Checks dependencies (tte, jq, alacritty)
  âœ“ Checks script exists (~/dotfiles/.config/hypr/scripts/screensaver)
  âœ“ Backs up hypridle.conf
  âœ“ Backs up WindowRules.conf
  âœ“ Adds listener to hypridle.conf
  âœ“ Adds window rules to WindowRules.conf
  âœ“ Makes scripts executable
  âœ“ Shows what was done
  âœ“ Provides rollback instructions

setup-omarchy-screensaver.sh:
  âœ“ Checks dependencies (tte, jq, alacritty)
  âœ“ Creates ~/.local/bin/ directory
  âœ“ Creates screensaver-cmd script
  âœ“ Creates screensaver-launch script
  âœ“ Creates screensaver ASCII art
  âœ“ Backs up hypridle.conf
  âœ“ Backs up WindowRules.conf
  âœ“ Adds listener to hypridle.conf
  âœ“ Adds window rules to WindowRules.conf
  âœ“ Shows what was done
  âœ“ Provides rollback instructions


ğŸ¬ EXECUTION FLOW (What Happens)
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

1. User doesn't interact for 150 seconds
2. Hypridle triggers: runs screensaver-launch
3. screensaver-launch detects monitors
4. Opens fullscreen terminal on each monitor
5. Terminal runs screensaver-cmd
6. screensaver-cmd starts TTE animation loop
7. User presses any key OR moves mouse
8. Animation stops, TTE exits, terminal closes
9. User back to normal Hyprland


ğŸ“Š COMPARISON: SYMPHONY vs OMARCHY
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

SYMPHONY:
  âœ“ Easier setup (uses existing scripts)
  âœ“ Single elegant display
  âœ“ Lower resource usage
  âœ“ Can't customize much
  Window class: Screensaver

OMARCHY:
  âœ“ More customizable
  âœ“ Can handle multiple monitors better
  âœ“ Full control over effects
  âœ“ Slightly more complex
  Window class: org.omarchy.screensaver


ğŸ’¡ PRO TIPS
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

1. Install TTE first
   sudo pacman -S python-terminaltexteffects

2. Test dependencies before setup
   which tte && which jq && which alacritty

3. Use Symphony first (easier)
   Then add Omarchy if desired

4. Monitor your backups
   ls -la ~/.config/hypr/*.backup.*

5. Reload carefully
   hyprctl reload (gentle)
   Super+Shift+R (keyboard shortcut)

6. Test immediately
   screensaver-launch

7. Customize after testing
   Change timeout, art, effects


